HEADWORD: Eariness
<hw>Ear"i*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scotch
<ets>ery</ets> or <ets>eiry</ets> affected with fear.]</ety> <def>Fear
or timidity, especially of something supernatural.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>eiryness</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sense of <qex>eariness</qex>, as twilight came on.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earing</ent>⟦br⟧
